    "Our experiments also suggest that it is important for the humans involved in these processes to have the skills, experience, and time to interpret and manage the information provided by the system (Ponce, 2022; Portela & Álvarez, 2022), to be informed about the error rate of the systems they supervise, and to have the ability (and the incentives) to be critical and to disagree with system decisions when necessary."
